{
    "question":"How Can I Tell If My Car Needs Maintenance?",
    "answer":"You can tell if your car needs maintenance by watching for warning signs like dashboard lights, unusual noises, or fluid leaks. Reduced fuel efficiency or vibrations while driving may also indicate potential issues. Regular maintenance, such as oil changes and tire checks, helps prevent major repairs. Keeping up with servicing ensures your car runs safely and efficiently."
}
